abstractText: The density of woody vegetation natural recruitment in floodplain restoration areas is measured to evaluate the development of restoration cover types toward the desired condition and to inform potential maintenance such as weed management.Data collection methods are described in Floodplain Vegetation Composition, Cover, and Woody Species Natural Recruitment Method #1310 [https://www.monitoringresources.org/Document/Method/Details/1310].
title: Floodplain Woody Species Natural Recruitment Data Analysis v1.0
